-- Russia Equity Movers: Inter RAO, Novatek, RusHydro, Transneft
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-06-07T15:50:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-07/russia-equity-movers-inter-rao-novatek-rushydro-transneft.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose 1.8
percent to 1,336.33 by the close in Moscow.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Novatek (NVTK RX) jumped 5.9 percent to 319.80 rubles,
the biggest gain since July 21.  Russia ’s second-biggest natural
gas producer may buy back up to $600 million shares in the next
twelve months, the company said. The stock rose 7 percent to
$107 in  London .  OAO RusHydro (HYDR RX) added 4.7 percent to 85.03 kopeks,
the strongest price since May 16. OAO Inter RAO UES (IRAO RX)
rose 1 percent to 2.7719 kopeks. The power utilities gained
after Russia’s Economy Minister Andrei Belousov said the state
will sell its entire stake in the companies by 2016.  OAO Severstal (CHMF RX) jumped 3 percent to 386.20 rubles,
the highest level since May 3. Russia’s second-largest steel
producer, jumped after Moody’s Investors Service raised the
company’s rating to one step below investment grade, citing
profitability and “healthy”  cash flow .  OAO Transneft (TRNFP RX) rose 4.2 percent to 44,341 rubles,
the biggest gain since May 24. Russia’s oil-pipeline operator
surged after the Economy Minister said the state will retain its
majority stake in the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
